title: DeBauge leads trio of Spartans at state golf
text:
DeBauge leads trio of Spartans at state golf The Emporia Gazette emporiagazette.com | 0 comments 
Emporia High’s Ashley DeBauge shot a 99 at Monday’s 5A state golf meet, coming two shots off the top 20 in her final high school meet. 
The Spartan senior was consistent between both sides of the Dubs Dread Golf Course in Kansas City, shooting a 50 on the front and a 49 on the back. Sara Mitchell followed for Emporia High with a 109, split between a 53 and a 56. Kylia Floyd rounded out Emporia’s qualifiers, carding a 126. 
CGHS finishes 10th in 3-2-1A 
Jordan Carlson posted a 108 to finish six shots off a medaling spot in the 3-2-1A state meet in Cheney. Her score led Council Grove, which finished 10th out of 12th teams on the Cherry Oaks Golf Course. 
Makenzie Downes posted a 122, followed closely by BrieAnna Grimmett’s 123. Kirsten Bane added a 137 to the Braves’ total, which rounded out at 490. Hailey Hower shot a 141 while Kylee Shafer notched a 164 for Council Grove as well.
